ick  is vice president of corporate finance and treasurer she joined devon in  and has held roles of increasing responsibility most recently as assistant treasurer and senior director of corporate finance tetrick previously worked at ford motor co whirlpool and hertz she holds a bachelor’s degree in mathematics from southwestern oklahoma state university and a master’s degree in business administration from the university of notre dame vice president tax james toups  joined devon as vice president of tax in march  toups previously worked for apache corp deloitte and arthur andersen he received both his bachelor’s and master’s degrees in accounting from texas am university his master’s degree includes a tax specialization toups is a board member of the oklahoma city chapter of texas executives inc he also is a member of the american institute of certified public accountants the texas society of certified public accountants and the american exploration and production council tax division  vice president and chief information officer ben williams  is vice president and chief information officer he joined devon in march  williams previously worked for kpmg marathon oil corp and pricewaterhousecoopers he is a graduate of rice university and has a bachelors degree in mechanical engineering williams is on the board of directors of energistics a global nonprofit consortium that helps develop and adopt dataexchange standards for the oil and gas industry vice president public and government affairs allen wright  is vice president of public and government affairs prior to joining devon in  he was director chief operating officer and vice president of public affairs at koch industriesflint hills resources and vice president of the fred and mary koch foundation wright serves on the boards of directors of the public affairs council and friends of the oklahoma history center he also is on the oklahoma state chamber of commerce executive committee and the oklahoma city chamber advi